cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving a deep neural ranking model for passage ranking, which is a task commonly studied in information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which falls under cs.CL. The proposed modifications to the model involve changes to the neural network architecture, which is a common topic in machine learning (ML) research, specifically in the sub-category of deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as attention mechanisms and feature engineering, which are also common in artificial intelligence (AI) research (cs.AI). Finally, the MS MARCO dataset used for evaluation contains text passages and queries, which are often studied in computer vision (CV) research, specifically in the sub-category of text recognition (cs.CV).
